# Visual Verification

## Always Screenshot After Layout or Sizing Changes

After any change involving layout, spacing, sizing, or responsive behavior, take a screenshot at **both mobile and desktop** before calling it done. Do not rely on reading code alone — broken layouts are obvious visually and not always obvious in code.

Use the browser tool:
1. Navigate to the affected page
2. Take a screenshot at desktop width (1440px)
3. Resize to mobile (600px) and take another screenshot
4. Fix any obvious issues before responding to the user

## When This Applies

- Any change to `flex`, `grid`, `width`, `height`, `padding`, `margin`, `gap`
- Any new responsive breakpoint or media query
- Any change to image sizing or positioning
- Any new component with layout styles

## What to Look For

- Text touching viewport edges (missing padding)
- Images overflowing their containers
- Elements stacking incorrectly at mobile
- Sections bleeding into each other visually
